{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we disable the DNN caching mechanism of Jellyfish.",
    "Evaluation metric It is non-trivial to isolate and measure the impact of DNN adaptation through main metrics (i.e., the accuracy and miss rates, as defined in Sect. 7.1) because of the interplay between various factors that affect these metrics.",
    "For example, a slight difference in the latency profiles between static and dynamic DNNs can lead to the selection of different DNN variants for execution, affecting the accuracy and/or end-to-end latency of clients.",
    "Hence, we define a specific metric called mismatch count.",
    "The mismatch count metric indicates the number of newly arrived inference requests (or frames) executed using the old DNN variant due to the delay in the DNN adaptation process."
  ]
}